wgputoy: tell wasm-pack's wasm-opt to accept ALL wasm features Rust emits

After cargo finishes the wasm32 build, wasm-pack runs binaryen's wasm-opt
to shrink the output. Rust 1.82+ enables increasing default-on wasm
features for wasm32-unknown-unknown (`bulk-memory`, `nontrapping-fptoint`,
`reference-types`, …). Binaryen's wasm-validator rejects features it
isn't told are allowed, with errors like:
  '[wasm-validator] memory.copy operations require bulk memory operations'
  '[wasm-validator] all used features should be allowed' (for trunc_sat_f32_u)

Rather than chase each feature as Rust enables more, pass `--all-features`
once. Discussion of trade-offs (vs whack-a-mole flags / skipping wasm-opt
/ bumping binaryen) is at github.com/utensil/forest/issues/55.

The pinned commit's Cargo.toml has no `[package.metadata.wasm-pack.profile.*]`
block (verified at 60d0bec); appending one is safe and additive.

Tracked: github.com/utensil/forest/issues/54 item 2, github.com/utensil/forest/issues/55.
To drop: upstream PR adding the metadata block, then bump
prep_wasm hash + flake pin.

diff --git a/Cargo.toml b/Cargo.toml
--- a/Cargo.toml
+++ b/Cargo.toml
@@ -78,3 +78,6 @@ wasm-bindgen-test = "0.3.31"
 # Tell `rustc` to optimize for small code size.
 opt-level = "s"
 strip = true
+
+[package.metadata.wasm-pack.profile.release]
+wasm-opt = ['-O', '--all-features']
